The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 13 February is 215,653 (24,855.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 08 February, there were 8,903 new confirmed cases (1,026.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 01 February, there were 10,913 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 18% (2,010 fewer cases).
